    "title": "Marian Anderson, public stages, and why rec centers matter",
    "publishedAt": "2026-05-17",
    "excerpt": "In 1939, Marian Anderson turned a denial into a national civic lesson: public spaces can become public stages. In 2026 Philadelphia, debates about arts funding and rec-center reinvestment ask the same question—who gets a place to be heard, to learn, and to belong?",
    "tags": [],
